The new Assert class throws the same exception as Java&#39;s assert keyword.
Another reason for having the new Assert class is that it lives in the same
package with the rest of the new JUnit classes. Because statics aren&#39;t
inherited, however, we have to duplicate the code to retain backwards
compatibility.

Sincerely yours,

Kent Beck
Three Rivers Institute 

